msgstr "如果您计划在 IO 线程上使用 `@PermissionsAllowed` ，请查阅 xref:security-proactive-authentication.adoc[“主动身份验证] ”中的相关信息。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`@PermissionsAllowed` is not repeatable on the class level due to a limitation with Quarkus interceptors.\n"
"For more information, see the xref:cdi-reference.adoc#repeatable-interceptor-bindings[Repeatable interceptor bindings] section of the Quarkus \"CDI reference\" guide."
msgstr "由于 Quarkus 拦截器的限制 `，@PermissionsAllowed` 无法在类级别上重复使用。有关详细信息，请参阅 Quarkus《CDI 参考指南》中的 xref:cdi-reference.adoc#repeatable-interceptor-bindings[“可重复的拦截器绑定”] 一节。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The easiest way to add permissions to a role-enabled `SecurityIdentity` instance is to map roles to permissions.\n"
"Use <<authorization-using-configuration>> to grant the required `SecurityIdentity` permissions for `CRUDResource` endpoints to authenticated requests, as outlined in the following example:"
msgstr "为启用了角色的 `SecurityIdentity` 实例添加权限的最简单方法是将角色映射到权限。请使用 ` <<authorization-using-configuration>> ` 方法，为经过身份验证的请求授予 `CRUDResource` 端点所需的 `SecurityIdentity` 权限，具体如下例所示："

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Add the permission `see` and the action `all` to the `SecurityIdentity` instance of the `user` role.\n"
"Similarly, for the `@PermissionsAllowed` annotation, `io.quarkus.security.StringPermission` is used by default."
msgstr "`将“see”` 权限和 `“all”` 操作添加到 `用户` 角色的 `SecurityIdentity` 实例中。同样，对于 `@PermissionsAllowed` 注解，默认使用 `io.quarkus.security.StringPermission` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Permissions `create`, `update`, and `read` are mapped to the role `admin`."
msgstr "`“创建”` 、 `“更新` ”和 `“读取”` 权限已映射到 `“admin”` 角色。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The role policy `role-policy1` allows only authenticated requests to access `/crud/modify` and `/crud/id` sub-paths.\n"
"For more information about the path-matching algorithm, see <<matching-multiple-paths>> later in this guide."
msgstr "角色策略 `role-policy1` 仅允许经过身份验证的请求访问 `/crud/modify` 和 `/crud/id` 子路径。有关路径匹配算法的更多信息，请参阅本指南后面的 <<matching-multiple-paths>> 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can specify a custom implementation of the `java.security.Permission` class.\n"
"Your custom class must define exactly one constructor that accepts the permission name and optionally some actions, for example, `String` array.\n"
"In this scenario, the permission `list` is added to the `SecurityIdentity` instance as `new CustomPermission(\"list\")`."
msgstr "您可以指定对 `java.security.Permission` 类的自定义实现。您的自定义类必须定义且仅定义一个构造函数，该构造函数接受权限名称，并可选地接受一些操作（例如 `String` 数组）。在此情况下，权限 `列表` 将通过 `new CustomPermission(\"list\")` 这种方式添加到 `SecurityIdentity` 实例中。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can also create a custom `java.security.Permission` class with additional constructor parameters.\n"
"These additional parameters get matched with arguments of the method annotated with the `@PermissionsAllowed` annotation.\n"
"Later, Quarkus instantiates your custom permission with actual arguments, with which the method annotated with the `@PermissionsAllowed` has been invoked."
msgstr "您还可以创建带有附加构造函数参数的自定义 `java.security.Permission` 类。这些附加参数会与带有 `@PermissionsAllowed` 注解的方法的参数相匹配。之后，Quarkus 会用实际参数实例化你的自定义权限，并调用注释为 `@PermissionsAllowed` 的方法。"

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Example of a custom `java.security.Permission` class that accepts additional arguments"
msgstr "一个接受额外参数的自定义 `java.security.Permission` 类的示例"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There must be exactly one constructor of a custom `Permission` class.\n"
"The first parameter is always considered to be a permission name and must be of type `String`.\n"
"Quarkus can optionally pass permission actions to the constructor.\n"
"For this to happen, declare the second parameter as `String[]`."
msgstr "自定义 `Permission` 类必须且仅有一个构造函数。第一个参数始终被视为权限名称，且必须为 `String` 类型。Quarkus 可以选择性地将权限操作传递给构造函数。若要实现这一点，请将第二个参数声明为 `String[]` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The `LibraryPermission` class permits access to the current or parent library if `SecurityIdentity` is allowed to perform one of the required actions, for example, `read`, `write`, or `list`."
msgstr "如果 `SecurityIdentity` 被允许执行某项所需操作（例如 `读取` 、 `写入或` `列出` ），则 `LibraryPermission` 类允许访问当前库或父库。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The following example shows how the `LibraryPermission` class can be used:"
msgstr "以下示例演示了如何使用 `LibraryPermission` 类："

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The formal parameter `update` is identified as the first `Library` parameter and gets passed to the `LibraryPermission` class.\n"
"However, the `LibraryPermission` must be instantiated each time the `updateLibrary` method is invoked."
msgstr "形式参数 `update` 被确定为第一个 `Library` 参数，并传递给 `LibraryPermission` 类。不过，每次调用 `updateLibrary` 方法时，都必须实例化 `LibraryPermission` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Here, the first `Library` parameter is `migrate`; therefore, the `library` parameter gets marked explicitly through `PermissionsAllowed#params`.\n"
"The permission constructor and the annotated method must have the parameter `library` set; otherwise, validation fails."
msgstr "这里，第一个 `Library` 参数是 `migrate` ；因此， `library` 参数通过 `PermissionsAllowed#params` 明确标记。权限构造函数和注释方法必须设置参数 `library` ，否则验证失败。"

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Example of a resource secured with the `LibraryPermission`"
msgstr "使用 `LibraryPermission` 保护的资源示例"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Similarly to the `CRUDResource` example, the following example shows how you can grant a user with the `admin` role permissions to update `MediaLibrary`:"
msgstr "与 `CRUDResource` 示例类似，以下示例演示了如何授予具有 `admin` 角色的用户更新 `MediaLibrary` 的权限："

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When building a native executable, the permission class must be registered for reflection unless it is also used in at least one `io.quarkus.security.PermissionsAllowed#name` parameter."
msgstr "在构建本地可执行文件时，权限类必须注册为反射类，除非至少有一个 `io.quarkus.security.PermissionsAllowed#name` 参数也使用了该类。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "We want to pass the `MediaLibrary` instance to the `LibraryPermission` constructor."
msgstr "我们希望将 `MediaLibrary` 实例传递给 `LibraryPermission` 的构造函数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Grants the permission `media-library`, which permits `read`, `write`, and `list` actions.\n"
"Because `MediaLibrary` is the `TvLibrary` class parent, a user with the `admin` role is also permitted to modify `TvLibrary`."
msgstr "`授予“media-library”` 权限，该权限允许 `执行读取` 、 `写入` `和列出操作` 。由于 `MediaLibrary` 是 `TvLibrary` 类的父类，因此具有 `admin` 角色的用户也被允许修改 `TvLibrary` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The `/library/*` path can be tested from a Keycloak provider Dev UI page, because the user `alice` which is created\n"
"automatically by the xref:security-openid-connect-dev-services.adoc[Dev Services for Keycloak] has an `admin` role."
msgstr "可以在 Keycloak 提供商的开发者界面 (Dev UI) 页面上测试 `/library/*` 路径，因为由 xref:security-openid-connect-dev-services.adoc[Keycloak 开发者服务] 自动创建的用户 `alice` 具有 `管理员` 角色。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The examples provided so far demonstrate role-to-permission mapping.\n"
"It is also possible to programmatically add permissions to the `SecurityIdentity` instance.\n"
"In the following example, xref:security-customization.adoc#security-identity-customization[`SecurityIdentity` is customized] to add the same permission that was previously granted with the HTTP role-based policy."
msgstr "到目前为止提供的示例演示了角色与权限的映射。此外，还可以通过编程方式向 `SecurityIdentity` 实例添加权限。在下面的示例中， xref:security-customization.adoc#security-identity-customization[对 SecurityIdentity进行了自定义] ，以添加与之前通过 HTTP 基于角色的策略授予的相同的权限。"

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Example of adding the `LibraryPermission` programmatically to `SecurityIdentity`"
msgstr "通过编程方式将 `LibraryPermission` 添加到 `SecurityIdentity` 的示例"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.8/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The permission `media-library` that was created can perform `read`, `write`, and `list` actions.\n"
